&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Registered General Band 5 Nurse&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A fantastic opportunity has become available for General Nurses to join the King&#39;s Staff Bank within the Ophthalmology department at Denmark Hill. We currently have lines of work available and you can start immediately! The duration of this placement will be until the end of March 2021.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join one of London&#39;s largest and busiest teaching hospitals as a valued member of the team and work shifts that suit you, with fuss-free online timesheets and weekly pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Available shift for Days, Evening, and Weekends. 37.5 Hours/ Week with option to have additional hours. The shifts are to cover more unsociable hours to fill COVID Lockdown Backlog.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this opportunity would suit you please get in touch ASAP!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Registered Nurse&lt;br /&gt; •NMC Registration&lt;br /&gt; •A minimum of 6 months experience working within the NHS&lt;br /&gt; •Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Bank nurses are invaluable to us and in return for their dedication and commitment, we offer the following benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Opportunities to work across sites, gaining invaluable knowledge and experience&lt;br /&gt; •Priority of shifts over agency workers &lt;br /&gt; •Onsite office and designated Business Partners to offer daily support&lt;br /&gt; •Ability to self-book shifts&lt;br /&gt; •Electronic Timesheet submission with weekly pay&lt;br /&gt; •An onsite recruitment, compliance and bookings team&lt;br /&gt; •Onsite office and designated Business Partners to offer daily support&lt;br /&gt; •Access to free Bank Partners Core Skills Training&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
